title: FWB's Fulmer tops field at Disney Classic race
text: FWB's Fulmer tops field at Disney Classic race Maddie Fulmer became the first Fort Walton Beach cross country runner ever to win the Disney Classic's elite race. By DAILY NEWS SPORTS STAFFsports@nwfdailynews.com By DAILY NEWS SPORTS STAFFsports@nwfdailynews.com Posted Oct. 11, 2015 at 5:35 PM Updated at 5:36 PM By DAILY NEWS SPORTS STAFFsports@nwfdailynews.com Posted Oct. 11, 2015 at 5:35 PM Updated at 5:36 PM Maddie Fulmer became the first Fort Walton Beach cross country runner ever to win the Disney Classic's elite race. Her time of 19 minutes, 15 seconds Saturday in the Maleficent Division helped Fort Walton Beach to a third-place finish, behind Hilton Head (S.C.) and Parkview, in the nine-team field. Brooke Crane (seventh 20:08) and Emma Rudman (eighth, 20:14) followed for the Vikings, who also had Jillian Hobbs (31st, 21:43) and Anna-Laura Chastain (36th, 21:50) as counting runners. Daniel Orcutt finished 29th in the elite boys race, the Captain Hook Division, with a time of 17:45. Jefferson Hobbs (32nd, 17:48) and Dillon Rice (63rd, 18:17) followed, with George McCann (78th, 18:28) and Stephen Jones (95th, 18:36) the other scoring runners for the 11th place-finishing Vikings. Fort Walton Beach finished fifth in the boys JV race, the Shere Khan Division, with Kadrin Cabrera (third, 17:34) leading the pack. Parker Dewrell (13th, 18:02) was the Vikings' other top-20 finisher. In the girls JV race, the Lady Tremaine Division, Jeanette Chastain (seventh, 22:31) led Fort Walton Beach to a third-place finish. Britney Roberts (14th, 23:12) and Maia Rivera (17th, 23:24) were the other top-20 finishers. By DAILY NEWS SPORTS STAFFsports@nwfdailynews.com By DAILY NEWS SPORTS STAFFsports@nwfdailynews.com Posted Oct. 11, 2015 at 5:35 PM Updated at 5:36 PM
